Description: Fragment of neck and sub-round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
Curator's comments: Pencil '483' and '262', circled. Name Kleudikos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 1108.37.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
